{{Quote|Sir, the possibility of successfully navigating an asteroid field is approximately three thousand seven hundred and twenty to one!''"<br />"''Never tell me the odds!|[[C-3PO]] and [[Han Solo]] on board the ''Millennium Falcon''|audio=3720to1-TheOdds.flac|<ref name="TESB" />}}
The '''Hoth asteroid field''', also known as the '''Hoth asteroid belt''' or '''Anoat Asteroid Belt''', was an [[asteroid field]] overlapping the boundaries of the [[Hoth system|Hoth]] and [[Anoat system]]s near the [[planet]] [[Hoth]].<ref name="TESB" />

==Description==
{{Quote|&hellip; and that, Lord Vader, was the last time they appeared in any of our scopes. Considering the amount of damage we've sustained, they must have been destroyed.''"<br />"''No, Captain. They're alive. I want every ship available to sweep the asteroid field until they are found.|[[Captain]] [[Lorth Needa]] and [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]]|<ref name="TESB" />}}
[[File:HothAsteroidChase-SWE.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The ''Millennium Falcon'' is pursued into the Hoth asteroid belt.]]
The Hoth [[Asteroid field|asteroid belt]] contained millions of [[asteroid]]s, some large, some small, some the size of tiny [[moon]]s. About two-thirds of them were big enough to destroy a [[starship]] as large as an [[YT-1300 light freighter]] on impact<ref name="SYWtBaJ?">''[[The Empire Strikes Back: So You Want to Be a Jedi?]]''</ref> and some were even large enough to devastate [[capital ship]]s.<ref name="TESB" /> Creatures the [[exogorth]] [[Sy-O]],<ref name="FACPOV">{{StoryCite|story=This Is No Cave|book=From a Certain Point of View: The Empire Strikes Back}}</ref> who lived within the "[[Big One]]" asteroid,<ref name="BMF 39" /> and [[mynock]]s were present in this area.<ref name="TESB" />

==History==
{{Quote|Our ships have sighted the ''Millennium Falcon'', my Lord. But it has entered an asteroid field and we cannot risk–''"<br />"''Asteroids do not concern me, Admiral. I want that ship, not excuses.|Admiral Piett and Darth Vader|<ref name="TESB" />}}
After the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]] was forced to [[Evacuation of Yavin 4|abandon]] [[Yavin 4]] after the [[Battle of Yavin]], they began a search for a new base. Eventually the rebels picked the [[planet]] [[Hoth]] as their new base, largely due to the existence of the asteroid field, as the asteroids in the [[Hoth system]] formed an effective barrier to outsiders.<ref name="BMF 39" />

[[File:PunyFalconRunsAway-ESBHD.jpg|thumb|right|285px|The Star Destroyer ''Avenger'' chases the ''Millennium Falcon'' out of the asteroid field.]]
Shortly after the [[Battle of Hoth]], being chased by the [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter]]s, the crew of the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]'' noticed that the [[hyperdrive]] was damaged, so they dashed into the asteroid belt to ditch the pursuit. Despite the near-impossibility of successfully navigating an asteroid field without getting pulverized, the ''Falcon'' evaded its pursuers (all of whom were destroyed by asteroid collisons) and hid inside one of the largest asteroids. [[Death Squadron]]&mdash;the Imperial [[fleet]] under the [[Commanding officer|command]] of [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] himself&mdash;pursued them, but the field punished them with brutal impacts, resulting in the loss of at least [[Ultimatum|one]] [[Star Destroyer]] when its [[Bridge (starship)|bridge]] tower was obliterated by a particularly large asteroid and even inflicting damage to the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought|''Executor''-class Star Dreadnought]] ''[[Executor]]'' before [[Admiral]] [[Firmus Piett|Piett]] informed Vader to make contact with [[Darth Sidious|Emperor Palpatine]], causing the ''Executor'' to withdraw from the asteroid field so that Vader could send a clear transmission.<ref name="TESB" />

